Income

Income is generated automatically.

Players receive income from every owned asset.

Income comes directly from the Bank.

Not from other players.

Income occurs before actions.

This allows players to immediately use newly earned capital.

Assets

Assets are permanent investments.

Buying an asset provides:

Recurring Income

Recurring Taxes

Long-term Growth

Assets form the backbone of the economy.

Players continuously evaluate:

Return on Investment

Risk

Future taxes

Market demand

Current Asset Structure
Asset	Purchase	Income	Tax	Max Per Player
Jack	30 LC	+10	-4	3
Queen	50 LC	+20	-6	3
King	80 LC	+30	-8	2
Ace	120 LC	+40	-10	2

These values may be tuned during playtesting but define Version 1's intended balance.

Why Assets Matter

Assets create the engine of your corporation.

Without assets:

No income.

No growth.

No long-term strategy.

Every corporation eventually becomes defined by its portfolio.

Taxes

Taxes exist for one purpose:

Prevent runaway leaders.

Without taxes:

The richest player becomes richer forever.

Taxes force difficult decisions.

Should I:

Buy another Ace?

Or keep cash?

Sell an asset?

Take another loan?

Taxes keep money moving.

Taxes occur:

Once per round.

After every player has completed their turn.

Not individually.

Everyone pays simultaneously.

Players always know upcoming taxes.

No surprises.

Loans

Loans are designed to create opportunity.

Especially early-game.

Without loans:

Growth becomes painfully slow.

Loans allow corporations to:

Expand faster

Buy stronger assets

Recover from mistakes

Prepare defenses

Fund investments

Loan Rules

Borrow from Bank.

Interest is fixed.

Repayment deadline exists.

Failure results in default.

Default eventually results in asset seizure if obligations cannot be met.

Loans are powerful.

But dangerous.

Investments

Players may invest in one another.

Investment contracts are negotiated.

Nothing is fixed.

Example:

"I'll give you 60 LC."

"You repay 90 LC in three rounds."

Both agree.

Contract created.

Automatically enforced.

Investments create:

Alliances

Political strategy

Financial dependency

Emergent gameplay

Market

The Bank maintains an unlimited supply of base assets.

Players never "run out" of assets globally.

However, the game transitions naturally into a player-driven economy as corporations mature.

Later in the match:

Trading

Auctions

Negotiations

Hostile Takeovers

become far more valuable than simply buying from the Bank.

This creates a natural evolution without forcing artificial scarcity.


