CORE DESIGN PHILOSOPHY

Every mechanic in Ledger must satisfy four principles:

Simple to understand. A new player should learn the basics within a few minutes.
Deep to master. Experienced players should continuously discover better strategies through negotiation, timing, investment decisions, and market control.
Meaningful choices. Every decision—borrowing, investing, buying, launching a takeover, or helping another player—should involve a real trade-off.
Player-driven stories. The most memorable moments should come from player interactions, not scripted events: desperate alliances, dramatic takeover defenses, risky investments, and unexpected betrayals.